Reference data origin from paper:
M. Niemel‰ and T. K‰rkk‰inen, "Improving clustering and cluster validation 
    with missing data using distance estimation methods," In: Computational 
    Sciences and Artificial Intelligence in Industry: New digital technologies 
    for solving future societal and economical challenges, Intelligent Systems, 
    Control and Automation: Science and Engineering. Springer Verlag, 2021. 
    (12 pages, to appear).

Description:
Data include min-max normalized, synthetic, S, Sim, and O data sets in a cell array. 
First cell is for different data sets (given in order S1, S2, S3, S4, Sim5D2, Sim2D2, 
O200, and O2000) and second cell is for different percentages (0, 5, 10, and 20%) of 
missing values generated to data. Values are missing completely at random (MCAR). 
Note that fully incomplete observations are discarded.  

